## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="0bb8c-109"><xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> puede dejar de responder cuando hay una transacción de ambiente y <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Complete%2A> se llama y posteriormente se revierte la transacción.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0bb8c-109"><xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> may hang when there is an ambient transaction and <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Complete%2A> is called and afterwards the transaction is rolled back.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0bb8c-110">Si <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> se llama antes de la finalización de la reversión de transacciones, una condición de carrera existirá, provocando la llamada a <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> deje de responder.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0bb8c-110">If <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> is called prior to the transaction rollback completing, a race condition will exist, causing the call to <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> to hang.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0bb8c-111">Esto puede ilustrarse con el siguiente ejemplo de pseudocódigo</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0bb8c-111">This can be illustrated by the following pseudo-code example</span></span>  
  
```  
using (TransactionScope ts = new TransactionScope())   
{  
   try  
   {  
       rc.Complete();  
      ...  
   }  
   Catch (Exception)   
   {  
      rc.Abandon()  
   }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="0bb8c-112">Esto no es el patrón recomendado para trabajar con <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0bb8c-112">This is not the recommended pattern for working with <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0bb8c-113">En su lugar el bloque try/catch debería colocarse fuera del ámbito de transacción.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0bb8c-113">Instead the try/catch block should be placed outside of the transaction scope.</span></span>

